<Review ID>2435118
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Outstanding MP3 Player
<Date>Mon Dec 24 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>I purchased the Sansa Clip 2GB about two weeks ago.  I was replacing an old 128 MB RCA MP3 Player.  I wanted something that was compatable with WMA files.  I did my research and found this player to have excellent reviews on numerous sites.  I have not been disappointed.  It is very easy to load music.  You can use Windows Explorer to drag and drop existing music files from your windows directories or you can use Windows Media Player to "Sync" music from your libraries.  I do wish that Windows Media Player was more user friendly, but that is not Sandisks problem.  Windows Media Player does allow you to Rip from CD and sync to the Sansa Clip without using Explorer.  I can't say enough about the sound quality.  With the built in equalizer, it is easy to customize the output.  I have been very impressed with the included earbuds.  I compared them with some Sony earbuds that I used with my previous player and the Sansa earbuds were superior by far.  I have been especially impressed with the range of the player/earbuds.  I can hear things in the music that I cannot hear with regular speakers.  When I first bought the player, I was thinking about buying some aftermarket earbuds, but I can't imagine that the sound could get significantly better than what I am getting with the included earbuds.  The phone plug on the earbuds was even gold plated.  I really like the display.  This gives you many options that would not be available without a display.  I can change settings, chose a particular song, navigate to different playlists, etc.  One thing I was disapointed with was the instructions.  I didn't think that it included enough instructions about loading music using Windows Media Player or about creating Playlists using Media Player. It took extra time to figure that out on my own.  Overall,  I have been extremely impressed by the Sansa Clip.  I would highly recommend it to anyone.  In fact, I just did a couple of days ago.  
<Overall>5

