<Review ID>5704055
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Gift from the Gods!!!
<Date>Tue Feb 12 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>My recommendation is to buy this MP3 Player. Did you hear that? I'll say it more clearly: BUY IT, BUY IT, BUY IT!!!!!!   Background: This is my first MP3 player. I had been using a portable, plastic casette player with some cheap Sony headphones that had good sound if I pressed the earpads against my ears but had a problem with one of the earpad clips always coming loose. Other than that, I have been listening to a cheap pair of Logitech speakers on the computer and a cd/casette no-brand cheapo player in my living room--not the best set-up for an audiophile wannabe, right?  So, I left my backpack somewhere along with the casette player, the Sony phones and a Chinese language casette. I have an 8 cd Chinese language set, so I decided it was time to transfer the CDs onto an MP3 player so I could practice on the go, whilst entering the 21st Century, technologically speaking. I researched and researched and researched some more and all roads led to this player. Following one reviewer's suggestion, I bought the 2 GB rather than than the 1 GB, which for me is more suitable because of the amount of storage I'd like to have with me.  So how is the player? Well, I'm ecstatic. This has to be a gift from the gods (for me anyway). The size of the unit (smaller than my thumb), the clip, the display, the incredible functionality, ease of setting-up, ease of downloading, ease of re-charging, are all worth the purchase price. This said, what is the most miraculous thing about this gem is the SOUND! It delivers wonderful and big sound with a clarity I have not heard in years--it is as if I am discovering music (and sound itself) for the first time and it is an experience I can only describe as sublime.  I have a varied music collection and this plays everything from Electronica to Classic Rock to Classical well with EQ settings you can change yourself. My greatest surprises have been with vintage rock albums, albums I suppose were first recorded on vinyl, which play superbly. I listened to T. Rex's Electric Warrior, and Crosby, Stills, Nash and Young's So Far last night and was amazed at hearing them and the music separation between the left and right phones--such a wonderful trip--listening to music as it was intended to be listened to--what a concept? Madonna's Ray of Light really allowed me to appreciate William Orbit's production--I heard things I had never heard before. Last but not least, my greatest amazement was listening to Opera. I selected the Classical EQ and listened to an Opera compilation CD entitled Aria: A Passion for Opera--the experience could only be described as revelatory. At one point I was listening to an aria from Puccini's Tosca and without warning tears just began flowing down my cheeks--all this from a player 1.25 x 2 inches. That experience alone was well worth the purchase price--everything that happens from here on is just GRAVY!  By the way, my 8 Chinese language CDs with about 8 hours of lessons, took no time to transfer to the Clip. 2 GB will hold about 30 hours of tunes and other material. The 2GB is actually for convenience, since you can easily delete from the device while it is attached to the computer so 1 GB would be fine if you don't mind the slight inconvenience of deleting music now and then--I'm telling you, this is really an amazing little device. The ipod shuffle suddenly seems like the stupid man or woman's portable music solution.  I have the player clipped to my collar and the earbuds in and I have to remember they're there. Whether listening to L'il Kim or Banco de Gaia, I'm groovin' with the sound. I have the black model, which I find aesthetically pleasing, and I just can't wait to experience the WOW! factor when I show this off to my friends.   Summation: 6 STARS on a 5 STAR scale   
<Overall>5

