<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Great bang for the buck.
<Date>Mon Jan 14 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>I bought this as a gift for a friend, so I don't actually own it. But I did get a chance to use it. For the price, you can't really go wrong. 2GB of storage, FM Tuner and cheaper than a iPod Shuffle. The sound quality is great compared to other budget players I have used in the past. Navigating through the menu was also a breeze. There really wasn't much to it.  My only gripe is that when playback is on random. If you advance tracks, it'll play random as well as if you go back a track. So if you accidentally skip a track you wanted to hear on random, you'll have to go back and search for it. Another thing I had trouble with was connecting to my computer. I've read a few other people having the same problem recognizing the device in Windows. Since its not my player, I wasn't going to lose sleep over it. My friend, however, didn't have any problems connecting.  
